  cochrane: { slug: "cochrane", name: "Cochrane", state: "Alberta", country: "Canada", region: "Cochrane, Bragg Creek, and the Calgary-Banff corridor", description: "A charming small town on the Bow River with one of Alberta's fastest growth rates", landmarks: ["First Street Downtown", "Spray Lake Sawmills Family Sports Centre", "Cochrane Ranche Historic Site", "MacKay's Ice Cream", "Sunset Ridge"], industries: ["retail", "professional services", "tourism", "construction", "real estate", "agriculture", "hospitality"], uniqueContent: ["Cochrane has transformed from a quiet ranching town into one of Alberta's fastest-growing communities, with its western heritage charm and proximity to both Calgary and the Rocky Mountains drawing thousands of new residents every year. First Street downtown is a walkable strip of boutique shops, cafes, and restaurants anchored by the iconic MacKay's Ice Cream — a destination that draws visitors from across the province. New developments like Sunset Ridge, Heartland, and Fireside have rapidly expanded the town's commercial footprint.", "The local economy revolves around the services that a growing residential population demands — dental clinics, home renovation contractors, real estate agents, and family-oriented retail. Cochrane's position on Highway 1A between Calgary and the mountains also makes it a tourism stop, benefiting restaurants and shops from Banff-bound traffic. The ranching and agricultural heritage still runs deep, with equestrian businesses and acreage services forming a niche but loyal market segment.", "Town Media Labs helps Cochrane businesses compete for the attention of a population that is growing faster than the local business community can keep up with. Our local SEO strategies ensure new residents find your Cochrane business before defaulting to Calgary options, while our Google Ads campaigns target the specific neighbourhoods where your customers live. We help Cochrane businesses build the kind of digital presence that matches the town's ambition — professional, community-rooted, and ready for growth."] },
